The paper deals with object shape detection in images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed model is based on a novel And-Or graph structure, which is a type of graphical model commonly used in computer vision. The paper also proposes a new optimization algorithm for training the model from weakly annotated data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as discriminative training, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed model is evaluated on several datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
